-- Standard Chartered Ghana Comprehensive Income Drops
-- B y   E m i l y   B o w e r s
-- 2012-02-29T10:38:24Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-28/standard-chartered-s-ghana-unit-says-2011-profit-dropped-26-.html
(Corrects to show comprehensive income in headline and
first paragraph of story published yesterday.)  Standard Chartered Bank Ghana Ltd.,
a lender in the West African nation, said total comprehensive
income for 2011 dropped 26 percent to 63.6 million cedis.  Net interest income declined to 150.4 million cedis from
152.7 million cedis a year earlier, the Accra-based unit of
Standard Chartered Plc said in a statement e-mailed by the Ghana
Stock Exchange today.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Emily Bowers at 
 ebowers1@bloomberg.net  